Description: Franchise Max provides a platform for franchisors and franchisees to use the same application to run their business smoothly.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Franchise Max provides a platform for franchisors and franchisees to use the same application to run their business smoothly. Franchisors can quickly setup new franchisees with the exact same processes. For marketing campaigns, CRM setup, project management, etc. All of this can be done with the click of a button and only takes minutes to do. There are many benefits for both the franchisor and the franchisee. The corporate office gets real-time data on all of their franchises. This includes everything from quotes/invoices to marketing campaigns. You can also see the communication history with all of their prospects and customers. No more waiting for quarterly meetings to find out how your franchisees are doing. You will have a bird’s-eye view on everything and in real-time. Ever need to make updates to processes and procedures or marketing campaigns for your franchises? Don’t worry about having timely meetings regarding these updates, or hoping your franchises even put in place these changes. It’s done with the click of a button from the corporate office and instantly updated across all franchises. Ever have a franchise close down? No worries. You can quickly reassign these contacts, along with all the communication history. You can assign everything to another franchise in the area or back to the corporate office. It's easy to reassign everything to another franchise when one opens nearby. Franchisees will love their franchisors, because everything is provided to them quickly and at ease. They won't have to worry about setting up a CRM, email marketing campaigns, etc. All of this is done with the click of a button from the corporate office and setup within minutes. Franchisees will also enjoy having real-time benchmark data shared with them from the corporate office on key metrics of other franchises in their region. Franchise Max is a win-win for everyone, with an easy to use platform that doesn’t take a tech wizard to understand it.

Description: ClaytonStress.com provides self-directed, online interactive computer therapy for traumatic stress.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: ClaytonStress.com provides online interactive computer therapy for traumatic stress including PTSD. The program is self-directed and does not require a traditional therapist. Users access the program from a personal computer 24/7. People who used a new on-line post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) program featuring Eye Movement Memory Processing (EMMP) reported, on average, a 43% reduction in PTSD symptoms and PTSD-like symptoms found in victims of traumatic events like combat, domestic violence, sexual abuse, urban violence, rape, and acts of nature. The patent-pending online program for PTSD symptoms and PTSD-like symptoms is offered by ClaytonStress.com, a web-based company founded to provide an online delivery platform for the relief of PTSD symptoms and related conditions.  The EMMP protocols were further refined by psychiatrist Thomas D. Geracioti, Jr., M.D., of the Cincinnati Veterans Administration Medical Center. EMMP is based on research showing that particular patterns of eye movement can be useful in relieving PTSD symptoms and other similar conditions. Comparative effectiveness studies have found that eye movement therapy was as effective as cognitive behavioral therapy in reducing PTSD symptoms.  Dr. Geracioti evaluated the ClaytonStress EMMP protocol with veterans diagnosed with PTSD. Before using the ClaytonStress.com program, the veterans rated their average distress levels at 7.44, on a scale of 1 (minimal stress) to 10 (maximum stress). After the program, the veterans reported average distress levels of 2.87. While the ClaytonStress.com program was in beta testing more than 1,500 individuals used it on-line. This group self-reported an average 43% reduction in their distress levels after a single on-line session. The group included active military, veterans, and non-military civilians.  Users access the ClaytonStress.com secure web site anonymously. No personal information is ever requested, although ClaytonStress.com does ask the userâ€™s military status, age, and gender. No therapist is required to complete the program; it is entirely self-directed. Users need only a computer with a sound card and a quiet place to follow the program protocols. It can also be used as an adjunct to traditional therapy. ClaytonStress.com offers multiple payment options for individual users and accepts credit cards. Personal information is not required for credit cards. A single session costs $10; a three-session plan is $25; a 10-session plan is $65; and a one-year unlimited sessions plan is $95. Users are limited on all plans to two sessions per 24-hour period.

Applications for these electro- magnetic products come from technology advances in motion control and the emerging fields of Active Noise and Vibration Control. These highly linear actuators are very cost effective as compared to competing technologies and offer a high output force to size relationship that favors many applications. Description: Audax Mezzanine invests in junior debt securities of private middle market businesses.

Full Description: Audax Mezzanine invests in junior debt securities of private middle market businesses with a history of cash flow stability, consistent revenue growth, strong management teams and a controlling shareholder with meaningful capital at risk. Since its founding in 2000, Audax Mezzanine has partnered with leading private equity firms to help finance their purchase of middle market companies. They provide junior capital, typically in the form of subordinated debt and unitranche loans, in addition to a co-investment in equity securities. They source opportunities directly from financial sponsors throughout North America, investing in leveraged buyouts, acquisition financings and debt recapitalizations. They differentiate themselves by taking a long-term view as it relates to new financings and portfolio decisions. Audax Mezzanine has an established track record of helping private equity firms acquire and grow businesses. Audax Mezzanine seeks a diverse portfolio of junior debt securities where they aim to be the sole or lead investor but will participate with other investors in certain circumstances. They invest across a broad range of industries and seek companies with revenue and cash flow stability, defensible market positions, experienced management teams, and strong equity sponsorship.

Description: Flowtune helps ops teams quickly resolve service degradation.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Software bugs, connectivity/hardware faults, misconfigurations, and human errors cause failures in cloud deployments at even the best-managed companies, costing hundreds of thousands of dollars in downtime and damaging a company’s reputation. Flowtune accelerates operators’ resolution of service degradation by pinpointing the true causes of failures quickly, and across the entire deployment environment from application regressions, through service under-provisioning, down to cloud provider failure. Flowtune collects a detailed “flight recording” of all communication between services using lightweight but powerful instrumentation techniques. Analytics on these detailed recordings then uncover the root cause of failure and trigger precise, actionable alerts. Alerts contain proposed mitigation plans; the user instructs Flowtune which plan to run with one click.

North America bounced back in 2011 with healthy growth of almost 4%, with the lion’s share from the premium anti-aging category, which grew by 14% in 2011 to reach $3.3 billion. In addition an article entitled Beauty Industry Analysis 2013 – Cost & Trends states – “the beauty industry continues to expand globally, with some projections claiming 8.5% growth by 2014”. Twitty Natural Products ™ has dedicated approximately 600 tons which equates 1.2 million pounds (to be sold on the market in 1.5, 3, and 5 ounces) of the mineral powder and includes an agreement to process, which is built into the cost.  The most interesting fact is the rarity of such a deposit in the United States, and in its natural state, the science carries a natural Ph balance proven by lab testing. The company has been in a testing phase for the last year and half, giving free samples to our testers in the market for consistent feedback.  This feedback is shown under the products tab of www.perfectporesclay.com, and in addition on facebook at Perfect Pores Clay® by Twitty Natural Products ™.   The market will consist of National Spa's, Wholesalers, Distributors, Trade Shows,  Consumers from Web purchases, and Retail Chain Stores Nationally. Marketing has begun by the way of social media and press releases to editors across the country. The addition of Perfect Pores Clay® to the market will meet a continued demand for natural products.
